Package: ACED
Type: Package
Title: Maximizing Accuracy of Cellular Deconvolution (ACED)
Version: 0.3.0
Author: person("Jonathan E.", "Bard",
  email = "jbard@buffalo.edu",
  role = c("cre", "aut"),
  comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0001-7433-0086"))
Maintainer: Jonathan Bard <jbard@buffalo.edu>
Description: ACED (Accurate Cellular Deconvolution) identifies the optimal
    clustering resolution of a single-cell RNA-seq reference dataset for the
    purpose of maximizing bulk RNA-seq deconvolution performance. It evaluates
    each resolution using the Approximate Cell Error (ACE) metric and supports
    full grid search (ACED), golden-section search (ACED_GS), and Brent's
    method (ACED_BRENT) optimization strategies.
